failed_tasks.reason: Critique: Try moving east again ("go east") to see if you reach the clearing, as your current location is still the forest.
Critique: Try using "look at tree" or "examine the trees" to prompt a more descriptive response from the game. If that fails, try "look" to see if the environment description mentions the trees.
Critique: Try "open mailbox" first, then "examine mailbox" again—sometimes the mailbox must be opened to reveal its contents or details.
Critique: Try searching for a key or another way to unlock the door before attempting to open it again. For example, "look under mat" or "examine surroundings" to find a way to unlock the door.
Critique: Try using "look under mat" or "move mat" to see if the game provides more information or reveals something hidden.
Critique: Try interacting with the egg in a different way, such as "open egg," "shake egg," or "examine egg closely" to see if you can trigger a more detailed response.

Critique: Try commands like "unlock grating with key" (if you have a key), "lift grating," or "look at grating" to get more information or interact with it differently. Make sure you have any required items to open it.

Critique: Try more direct commands like "go through window" or "enter the window" until the game confirms you are inside or in a new location. If the window is not accessible, examine it or look for another way in.
Critique: Try using commands like "look outside," "look beyond window," or "look out window" to prompt the game for a more specific description of what is visible through the open window.

Critique: Try to find the key (often under the mat), then return to the front door and use "unlock door" followed by "open door". If already holding the key, use "open door" while at the front door location.

Critique: Try examining your surroundings for possible exits, or use "look" to find a path east. If east is blocked, consider alternative directions or commands like "go southeast" or "enter clearing" if available.

Critique: Try using "go down," "descend," or look for another way to climb down—perhaps there is a specific path, ledge, or object to interact with. Use "look" to examine the area for clues on how to safely descend into the canyon.
Critique: Try opening the egg or using "look closely at egg" to see if a more detailed description or hidden feature is revealed.
Critique: Try interacting with the egg in different ways, such as "look closely at egg," "inspect egg," or "examine jewels," to see if a more detailed description is revealed.
Critique: Try "examine birds nest" or "look at birds nest" explicitly, as the game may require the full object name to provide a description.
Critique: Try examining the area for a key (e.g., "look under mat" and then "take key" if found), then "unlock door" and "open door" to open the front door.
Critique: Try "go east" or "open door" if a door is blocking your way, then attempt "east" again. Make sure there are no obstacles preventing movement.
Critique: Try "look at welcome mat" or "examine welcome mat" again, and ensure you receive a descriptive response about the mat, not just the game's welcome message.
Critique: Try examining the nest in a different location, or with the egg (if present) inside it. You might also try "look at egg" if there is one, or "search nest" for more details.
Critique: Try using "open jewel-encrusted egg" again, or consider examining the egg for a hidden mechanism, or using another item (like "examine egg closely" or "use [object] on egg") to open it.
Critique: Try using "look at grating" or "look at grate" again, or check if you are in the correct location to see the grating. Ensure the object is present in your environment before examining.

WELCOME TO ZORK

    ZORK is a game of adventure, danger, and low cunning.  In it you will explore some of the most amazing territory ever seen by mortal man.  Hardened adventurers have run screaming from the terrors contained within!

    In ZORK the intrepid explorer delves into the forgotten secrets of a lost labyrinth deep in the bowels of the earth, searching for vast treasures long hidden from prying eyes, treasures guarded by fearsome monsters and diabolical traps!

    No PDP-10 should be without one!

    ZORK was created at the MIT Laboratory for Computer Science, by Tim Anderson, Marc Blank, Bruce Daniels, and Dave Lebling.  It was inspired by the ADVENTURE game of Crowther and Woods, and the long tradition of fantasy and science fiction adventure.  ZORK was originally written in MDL (alias MUDDLE).  The current version was translated from MDL into Inform by Ethan Dicks <erd@infinet.com>.

    On-line information may be available using the HELP and INFO commands (most systems).

    Direct inquiries, comments, etc. by Net mail to erd@infinet.com.

                     All rights reserved.

Up a Tree
You are about 10 feet above the ground nestled among some large branches.  The nearest branch above you is above your reach.
On the branch is a small birds nest.
In the bird's nest is a large egg encrusted with precious jewels, apparently scavenged somewhere by a childless songbird.  The egg is covered with fine gold inlay, and ornamented in lapis lazuli and mother-of-pearl.  Unlike most eggs, this one is hinged and has a delicate looking clasp holding it closed.  The egg appears extremely fragile.
You hear in the distance the chirping of a song bird.

>                                                                                                                                ForestScore: 15Moves: 109

Canyon View
You are at the top of the Great Canyon on its south wall.  From here there is a marvelous view of the Canyon and parts of the Frigid River upstream.  Across the canyon, the walls of the White Cliffs still appear to loom far above.  Following the Canyon upstream (north and northwest), Aragain Falls may be seen, complete with rainbow. Fortunately, my vision is better than average and I can discern the top of the Flood Control Dam #3 far to the distant north.  To the west and south can be seen an immense forest, stretching for miles around.  It is possible to climb down into the canyon from here.
